        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>March 5.</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have directed M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray to send to you a copy of the “Origin”, &amp; I hope it may in some degree interest you.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Sir | Yours faithfully | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3466.xml" resp="#automat">letter from G. E. Harris, 3 March 1862</ref> (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 10).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3466.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter of 3 March 1862</ref> (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 10), Harris had requested a copy of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> because he could not afford to buy it. John Murray was CD’s publisher. This letter was found inside a copy of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> 3d ed.</note>
        </div>        
            
